From 79fb4ab57ff81a7279be88cf0334bd584109de78 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Richard Gibbs <wofderfs@googlemail.com>
Date: Tue, 9 Jun 2026 23:20:17 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] jam.c: enable the real sun.misc.Launcher system
 classloader on AmigaOS

The earlier "no-output heisenbug" was missing openjdk natives (CDS stubs,
VM.latestUserDefinedLoader0, TimeZone, getManifestNum), not memory corruption;
with those supplied the system loader initialises reliably.  Use it (with a
bootstrap-loader fallback if init fails); -Xbootclasspath classes load via
delegation.  Known gap: app classes from a -classpath entry (URLClassPath) still
fail on Amiga volume:->URL conversion.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 src/jam.c | 23 ++++++++++++-----------
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+), 11 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/jam.c b/src/jam.c
index 2951d20..eccffab 100644
--- a/src/jam.c
+++ b/src/jam.c
@@ -274,17 +274,18 @@ int main(int argc, char *argv[]) {
     }
 
 #ifdef __amigaos4__
-    /* The OpenJDK system classloader (sun.misc.Launcher) now INITIALISES cleanly
-       on AmigaOS -- the hard crash in getSystemClassLoader was the missing CDS
-       JVM_GetResourceLookupCacheURLs/JVM_KnownToNotExist (libjava.so called the
-       unresolved symbols); those are now stubbed (return NULL/FALSE) in jvm.c.
-       HOWEVER running the app class THROUGH the system loader still has a latent
-       bug (HelloWorld loads + main returns but produces no output; a heisenbug
-       that the [NM] debug trace masked -> suspect memory corruption / GC on the
-       much larger Launcher/URLClassPath code path).  So for now keep the reliable
-       BOOTSTRAP path (app class on -Xbootclasspath).  TODO(Phase 3): debug the
-       system-loader run path + Amiga path->URL for real -classpath. */
-    system_loader = NULL;
+    /* The OpenJDK system classloader (sun.misc.Launcher) now initialises reliably on
+       AmigaOS -- the earlier "heisenbug" was missing openjdk natives (CDS stubs,
+       VM.latestUserDefinedLoader0, TimeZone, ...), now supplied.  Use the real system
+       loader; classes on -Xbootclasspath load via delegation.  Fall back to the
+       bootstrap loader if it ever fails to init.  KNOWN GAP: loading an app class from
+       a -classpath entry (URLClassPath) still fails -- Amiga "volume:" path -> URL
+       (Phase 3 TODO); -Xbootclasspath is the working path meanwhile. */
+    system_loader = getSystemClassLoader();
+    if(system_loader == NULL)
+        clearException();
+    else
+        mainThreadSetContextClassLoader(system_loader);
 #else
     if((system_loader = getSystemClassLoader()) == NULL)
         goto error;
