From e2b4d148d6b362166ce208582d557202a455130c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Richard Gibbs <wofderfs@googlemail.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 07:36:47 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] Amiga path model: strip leading "/Volume:" in JVM_Open +
 nativeLibOpen

java.io presents canonical paths as Unix-absolute ("/Volume:dir/file") so
File.isAbsolute()/toURI() don't double the Amiga path (the -classpath/URL bug).
The native file-open chokepoints strip the leading '/' (and "./") back to a real
AmigaDOS path: JVM_Open (ZipFile/JarFile and friends open through it) and
nativeLibOpen (loadLibrary/dlopen).  With this + the openjdk-natives path
adaptations, File/URL round-trips and direct JarFile/ZipFile opens work on Amiga.
(Full URLClassLoader -classpath still blocked by sun.nio.fs platform detection.)

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 src/classlib/openjdk/jvm.c | 13 +++++++++++++
 src/os/amiga/os.c          | 15 +++++++++++++--
 2 files changed, 26 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/classlib/openjdk/jvm.c b/src/classlib/openjdk/jvm.c
index bfbbb93..668a476 100644
